{
  "stem": "10698.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's when I found out that they are-- they are alive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then they started to send us packages with food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So between the-- between the better ration card, and the packages, we were not starving.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were-- we-- so I met my husband, and we got married in 1946.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Berlin.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time by then, we rented an apartment to stay.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and-- and we did the wedding right there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We invited some people, and some people that were, you know, German-Jewish people that came back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they helped us out with putting together little foods and things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they opened up a kosher butcher stores, and we could buy it on the ration cards, also.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they chipped in with ration cards for the-- and-- and so we got married.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- and a very religious German-Jewish people were the witnesses and things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lost track.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- and-- the-- so we got married.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then, my brother sent, you know, to bring us to the United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I became pregnant right away-- nine and a half months later, my son was born.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when I became pregnant, they said for me to wait until I gave birth to my son.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They want to see what kind of child I give birth to-- if it's a normal child.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Jewish doctor from the Iranian-Jewish hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He took care of me-- I can't begin to tell you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because you know, any people that came out from the camps-- first of all, when I stood up and put my legs together, I didn't think that they're supposed to-- flesh was supposed to meet flesh.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Eventually it did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's how undernourished we were when we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm going to tell you one more thing about the racism of Polish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One time we were--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one time my sister and I, we are standing at one of-- coming from Munich towards Berlin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were waiting-- maybe we will get on a train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were some people sitting around waiting, also.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we got to talking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were talking Polish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And education in-- for Jewish kids in Warsaw was more like the refined English you hear like from England or South Africa.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Do you know that my sister-in-law talked to a man, a Polish man, during the time when they started to send people to the camps and into the ovens.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, God, that's a-- that is the most delicious smell-- the Jewish fat frying.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't hear it from a strange person-- my own sister-in-law.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't even know she was Jewish at the time when he told her that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the kind of-- I'm not saying that all Polish people are bad.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had people that used to come to our home where they were friends that they would kill for us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they participated in dinners, and they used to keep their heads or caps on because of respect for my father-- because he was wearing a cover on his head during the meal time.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- so we finally came from-- from-- excuse me-- from Bremen to the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On a ship that was-- oh, how that ship didn't drown, I'll never know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was so sick-- Marlin, Marlene, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's surprising it didn't drown.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was so sick all-- the whole time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my poor child-- he was in diapers, you know, it was burnt and all.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and my brother picked us up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "April the 10th 1948.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just before Pesach.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At my brother's house.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strange.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Honey, for years, you-- we didn't know about the holiday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know about the Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know about anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The first time I started with [NON-ENGLISH], that I didn't have all the pots and pans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when-- when I was in Berlin, and when we had started to have a kosher butcher, that was the first time I tasted a piece of kosher meat.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember, during a Seder, when my brothers used to-- when you read.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they would used to go trying to mumble a little bit.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father used to go like, ahem, ahem.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because he wanted to hear them out loud.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So you see, certain things you start remembering during the holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And those are the worst times.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were happy times.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In New York?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, I went into-- I didn't want to stay with my brother because, you know, some wives cannot be-- not the second.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His second wife was marvelous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm still friends with her, even though my brother is dead.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She lives in Las Vegas.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
